# Internationalization (i18n) Rules

## Supported Languages

- English (en) - Default
- Hebrew (he) - RTL

## Setup

Using i18next + react-i18next

## Usage

### In Components

```typescript
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

export function MyScreen() {
  const { t } = useTranslation();
  
  return (
    <View>
      <Text>{t('groups.title')}</Text>
      <Text>{t('groups.createGroup')}</Text>
    </View>
  );
}
```

### Translation Files

Located in `apps/mobile/i18n/locales/`

**en.json:**
```json
{
  "groups": {
    "title": "Groups",
    "createGroup": "Create Group"
  }
}
```

**he.json:**
```json
{
  "groups": {
    "title": "קופות",
    "createGroup": "פתח קופה"
  }
}
```

## Rules

### NO Hardcoded Strings

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
<Text>{t('common.loading')}</Text>

// ❌ WRONG
<Text>Loading...</Text>
```

### Organize by Feature

```json
{
  "common": { ... },
  "groups": { ... },
  "history": { ... },
  "profile": { ... }
}
```

### Use Descriptive Keys

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
t('groups.noGroups')

// ❌ WRONG
t('msg1')
```

## Changing Language

```typescript
import { changeLanguage } from '../i18n';

await changeLanguage('he');
```

## RTL Support

Hebrew automatically enables RTL layout.
Language changes may require app restart.
